 Since $f(x)=\frac{a}{1-x}$, we can find $f^{-1}(x)$ by interchanging $x$ and $y$ and solving for $y$:
\begin{align*}
y &= \frac{a}{1-x} \\
x &= \frac{a}{1-y} \\
1-y &= \frac{a}{x} \\
y &= 1-\frac{a}{x} \\
f^{-1}(x) &= 1-\frac{a}{x}
\end{align*}
Since $f(-1)=f^{-1}(4a+1)$, we have
\begin{align*}
\frac{a}{1-(-1)} &= 1-\frac{a}{4a+1} \\
\frac{a}{2} &= \frac{-3a}{4a+1} \\
a &= -2
\end{align*}
Thus, the product of all possible values of $a$ is $-2$. </think> <answer> $-2$. </answer>

